Interaction value:
opportunities for learning (Austin, 2000b; Googins & Rochlin, 2000; Huxham, 1996; Yajizi & Doh, 2009); development of unique capabilities and knowledge creation (Googins & Rochlin, 2000; Gray, 1989; Hardy, Phillips, & Lawrence, 2003; Huxham, 1996; Porter & Kramer, 2011; Yaziji & Doh, 2009); access to networks (Heap, 1998; Millar et al., 2004; Yaziji & Doh, 2009); greater technical expertise (Austin, 2000a; Seitanidi, 2010; Vock et al., 2011); increased ability to change behavior (Le Ber & Branzei, 2010a, 2010b; Stafford et al., 2000);
improved relations with profit sector (Austin, 2000a; Vock et al., 2011); market intelligence (Austin, 2000b; Yaziji & Doh, 2009).
